author: Inside Edition
description: Grace Meyers from Michigan is living with Marfan syndrome. The inherited disorder affects someone's connective tissue, according to the Mayo Clinic. For Grace, this comes with several life-threatening medical complications, including an enlarged aorta that could tear at any moment. In addition, she also has a noticeably taller and more slender build. "I definitely still deal with daily anxiety and fear of what has occurred and what could occur," she told Inside Edition Digital's Andrea Swindall.
title: Michigan Woman Has Rare Disorder That Could Tear Aorta At Any Moment
